CXMOD Installation
==================

REQUIREMENTS
------------
  - Linux kernel 3.10 or later
  - gcc (or compatible C99 compiler)
  - make
  - Root access for install and tuning operations

QUICK INSTALL
-------------
  tar -xzf CXMOD.tar.gz
  cd cx-2.0.0
  make
  sudo make install

  Or using the install script:
  sudo ./scripts/install.sh

CUSTOM PREFIX
-------------
  make
  sudo make install PREFIX=/opt/cxmod

  Installs to /opt/cxmod/sbin/cxmod

PACKAGE BUILD (DESTDIR)
-----------------------
  make
  make install DESTDIR=/tmp/staging PREFIX=/usr

  Produces files under /tmp/staging for packaging.

CROSS-COMPILE
-------------
  make CC=aarch64-linux-gnu-gcc    # ARM64
  make CC=arm-linux-gnueabihf-gcc  # ARM32
  make CC=riscv64-linux-gnu-gcc    # RISC-V
  make CC=mips-linux-gnu-gcc       # MIPS

UNINSTALL
---------
  sudo make uninstall

VERIFY
------
  cx version
  sudo cx diagnose
